ot of people have been requesting long, curly hair. So I made a retouched version of the very unpopular Tiara Wig. It comes with a separate accessory flower to make it a little cuter. No tiara, sorry. (If you do not want the flower accessory you can choose not to use it)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="cf0"&gt;This mod is an override of the "&lt;b&gt;Tiara Wig&lt;/b&gt;" from &lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;New Leaf.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The flower replaces the "Post-op patch" from New Leaf. This wig is fully compatible with all colors, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cf0"&gt;skintones&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cf0"&gt;, and devices &lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;(Luma &amp;amp; Citra Tested/Compatible)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="cf0"&gt;There are two colors for the flower accessories (Pink &amp;amp; Red) Only download ONE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="cf0"&gt;Please follow the tutorial inside the zipped folder if you need help on how to install them in your game &lt;b&gt;(The tutorial has been updated!!!)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="cf0"&gt;All I ask is that you download this mod for free personal use and not for commercial (don't put it behind a paywall, post without permission, etc.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="cf0"&gt;!!!FOR 2DS/3DS USERS, PLEASE READ BELOW!!!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="cf0"&gt;For some reason, the red flower isn't working on my 3Ds (it's glitching out) So the red flower will be for C&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cf0 SelectedElement"&gt;itra&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cf0"&gt; users ONLY. The pink flower and hair is working fine.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="cf0"&gt;Thank you so much for shopping at my boutique! Stay glamorous.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="cf0"&gt;-Mikki&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cf1"&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;♡&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
